To create a local git repository:
S1.Install git to your system.
S2.To initialise a directory as git use "git init" command
S3.To add files to this directory use "git add ."
The above step will add all the files into git
S4.To add your remote repo as origin use "git remote add origin "your repository""
S5. To add files from your local repo to remote repo use push command "git push - origin main"
